document_data.Notable Owners:
[[File:Strahd's organ.png|thumb|''[[Strahd von Zarovich]]'s mighty organ.''|350x350px]]
Pipe organs were often most appreciated by human communities; however, because of their size, price, and complexity, only the most wealthy could afford them.

*[[Dwalimar Omen]]: the [[wizard]] captain of the ''[[Realms Master]]'' ship that traversed the realms via one of the ''Astrolabes of Nimbral'' in the late 14{{th}} century [[DR]].{{Cite dragon/247/Rogues Gallery: Crew of the Realms Master|75}}
*[[Halaster Blackcloak]]: constructed a monstrous pipe organ out of stalagmites and [[marble]], placed within his Music Hall. It's sound magically carried across the entire temple but was magically confined to the structure.
*[[Skoradin Thinskin]]: a disenfranchised [[gnome]] [[rogue]]-turned-[[cleric]] of [[Talos]] who played his rueful pipe organ on board of the [[paddleboat]] called ''[[the Frothing Miscreant]]'' to bring doom to [[Cormyr]] in the mid-14{{th}} century [[DR]].{{Cite dungeon/80/The Frothing Miscreant|30-31}}
*[[Strahd von Zarovich]]: the master of the [[Castle Ravenloft]] had a sinister-sounding pipe organ inside his castle's dining hall.
